A central event in the formation of this group was the adoption of the Great Law of Peace. This
group agreed to a series of treaties with the British collectively called the Covenant Chain, and this group
fought against the French over control of the fur trade in the Beaver Wars. The Tuscarora joined this
group in 1722, leading this group to adopt the nickname the Six Nations. Hiawatha was a leader of, for
the point, what confederacy of northeastern Native American tribes?=====
Iroquois Confederacy =====